function handleSearch() {

  $('.search-bar .form-control').focus(function () {
    $(this).closest('.search-bar .input-group').addClass('has-focus');
  });
  $('.search-bar .form-control').focusout(function () {
    $(this).closest('.search-bar .input-group').removeClass('has-focus');
  });

  const closeButton = '<button type="button" class="search-bar-close" onclick="closeSearch();"><i class="ft ft-close"></i></button>';
  $(closeButton).prependTo('.search-bar-mobile');

  $('.search-bar-mobile').show();

}

function handleStickyNav() {
  let headerHeight;
  let outerHeaderHeight;
  let scrollTop;
  let screenWidth;
  let hasNav;

  if ($('NAV .navbar-nav li').html()) {
    hasNav = true;
  } else {
    hasNav = false;
  }

  applyStickyNav();
  $(window).scroll(() => {
    applyStickyNav();
  });

  function applyStickyNav() {
    headerHeight = $('#MPimage').height();
    outerHeaderHeight = $('#HEADER').height() - 50;
    screenWidth = $(window).width();
    scrollTop = $(document).scrollTop();

    if (document.getElementById('admin-toolbar')) {
      $('.nav-L1').css('top', 30);
    }

    if (scrollTop > headerHeight
            && screenWidth > 767) {
      $('.nav-L1').addClass('sticky-header');
      $('#l1navghostcontainer').css('display', 'block');
      $('.hero').addClass('has-sticky');
    } else {
      $('.nav-L1').removeClass('sticky-header');
      $('#l1navghostcontainer').css('display', 'none');
      $('.hero').removeClass('has-sticky');
    }

    if (scrollTop > outerHeaderHeight
            && hasNav) {
      $('#NAV').addClass('sticky-header');
      $('#MPOuter').addClass('has-sticky');
    } else {
      $('#NAV').removeClass('sticky-header');
      $('#MPOuter').removeClass('has-sticky');
    }
  }
}

function handleLoggedOutRedirectLink() {
  if ($('.HLWelcome #Welcome_NotLoggedIn').length) {
    const topNavLoginHref = $('#MPheader .user-icon ul li a').attr('href');
    const returnURI = topNavLoginHref.indexOf('openid&state=');
    const mainURLWithoutRedirect = topNavLoginHref.slice(0, returnURI + 13);
    const currentLocation = window.location.href;

    const slash = /\//ig;

    const colon = /:/g;

    const ampersand = /&/ig;

    const underscore = /_/ig;

    const currentSanitizedURI = currentLocation.replace(slash, '/').replace(colon, ':').replace(ampersand, '&').replace(underscore, '_');

    const newCompleteURL = mainURLWithoutRedirect + currentSanitizedURI;
    $('#MPheader .user-icon ul li a').attr('href', newCompleteURL);
    $('.hero.make-buttons em a').attr('href', newCompleteURL);
    $('.left-rail .make-buttons.login-msg em a').attr('href', newCompleteURL);

    // for hero area login button 12/15/2022
    const ibmbuttonElement = document.querySelector('ibmc-hero ibmc-hero-cta-1 ibmc-button');
    if (ibmbuttonElement) {
      const ibmcbuttonShadowRoot = ibmbuttonElement.shadowRoot;
      if (ibmcbuttonShadowRoot) {
        const logInALink = ibmcbuttonShadowRoot.querySelector('a');
        if (logInALink) {
          logInALink.href = newCompleteURL;
          logInALink.target = '_self';
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

/* Equal height for featured-area -  12/01/2021  */
$.fn.equalHeights = function () {
  let max_height = 0;
  $(this).each(function () {
    max_height = Math.max($(this).height(), max_height);
  });
  $(this).each(function () {
    $(this).height(max_height);
  });
};

  setTimeout(() => {
    handleLoggedOutRedirectLink();
  }, 2000);

  /* 10/19/2022: Search section in TOP header */
  const handleCustomSearch = ((target) => {
    window.open(`https://www.ibm.com/search?q=${target.val().trim()}`, '_blank');
    target.val('');
  });
  const validateCustomInput = ((target) => (!!target.val().trim()));

  $('.custom_SearchButton').click((e) => {
    const target = $(`.${$(e.currentTarget).data('customsearchterm')}`);
    validateCustomInput(target) && handleCustomSearch(target);
  });
  $('.custom_SearchTerm').add('.customMobile_SearchTerm').on('keydown', (e) => {
    if (e.key == 'Enter') {
      validateCustomInput($(e.currentTarget)) && handleCustomSearch($(e.currentTarget));
      e.preventDefault(); return false;
    }
  });
});

const setDrapeText = () => {
  const [heroBanner] = document.getElementsByTagName('ibmc-hero');

  if (heroBanner) {
    const drape = heroBanner.shadowRoot.querySelector('#ibmc-hero-news');

    const [text] = drape.getElementsByClassName('ibmc-hero-news-link');

    const [svg] = drape.getElementsByTagName('svg');

    const name = document
      ?.querySelector('.ibm-community-future-event-details_event-name .HtmlContent p')
      ?.innerHTML;

    const url = document
      ?.querySelector('.ibm-community-future-event-details_event-url .HtmlContent p')
      ?.innerHTML;

    if (url && url.length > 0) {
      text.href = url;
    }

    if (name && name.length > 0) {
      text.innerHTML = name;
      text.appendChild(svg);
    }
  }
};

window.onload = () => {
  setDrapeText();
};</script>

<div class="HtmlContent"><style>
body.no-scroll {
  overflow: hidden;
}

#menu_top-container {
  background: white;
  color: #323232;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  font-family: "IBM Plex Sans", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, sans-serif;
  font-size: 14px;
  left: 0;
  position: relative;
  top: 0;
  width: fit-content;
  z-index: 1000;
}
#menu_top-container #menu_overlay {
  background-color: rgba(22, 22, 22, 0.5);
  display: none;
  height: 100%;
  left: 0;
  top: 0;
  position: fixed;
  opacity: 1;
  transition: opacity 0.24s cubic-bezier(0.2, 0, 0.38, 0.9) 0s, background-color 0.24s cubic-bezier(0.2, 0, 0.38, 0.9) 0s;
  width: 100%;
  z-index: 1;
}
#menu_top-container #menu_overlay.visible {
  display: block;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_mobile_icon {
  display: none;
}
#menu_top-container *:not(#menu_buttons_container).visible {
  display: block;
}
#menu_top-container ul {
  list-style-type: none;
}
#menu_top-container a {
  border: none;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  color: #161616;
  display: flex;
  text-decoration: none;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_button {
  background: white;
  padding: 0.8125rem var(--cds-spacing-05, 1rem);
}
#menu_top-container .menu_button svg, #menu_top-container #menu_mobile-button svg {
  margin: auto 0;
  margin-left: 0.5em;
  transition: all 0.2s;
}
#menu_top-container a:hover,
#menu_top-container .menu_left li a:hover,
#menu_top-container .menu_sub-links li a:hover {
  background: #e5e5e5;
  cursor: pointer;
}
#menu_top-container #menu_buttons_container {
  background: white;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  height: fit-content;
  z-index: 9;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_root {
  background: white;
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 25% 75%;
  left: 0;
  min-height: 20rem;
  overflow-y: scroll;
  overflow-x: hidden;
  position: fixed;
  transition: all 0.2s;
  width: 100vw;
  z-index: 3;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_root.hidden {
  height: 0;
  min-height: 0;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_root #menu_close_button {
  background: none;
  border: none;
  cursor: pointer;
  height: fit-content;
  position: absolute;
  right: 1rem;
  top: 1rem;
  width: fit-content;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_root #menu_close_button:hover {
  background: #e5e5e5;
}
#menu_top-container #menu_mobile-button {
  background-color: var(--cds-ui-background, #fff);
  border: 2px solid transparent;
  cursor: pointer;
  display: none;
  height: 3rem;
  transition: background-color 0.11s ease 0s, border-color 0.11s ease 0s;
  position: absolute;
  z-index: 9;
}
#menu_top-container #menu_mobile-button:hover {
  background-color: var(--cds-hover-ui, #e5e5e5);
  transition-duration: 95ms;
}
#menu_top-container #menu_mobile-button[expanded=true] > svg {
  transform: rotate(180deg);
}
#menu_top-container #menu_mobile-button-burger-icon,
#menu_top-container #menu_mobile-button-close-icon {
  display: none;
  margin: auto;
}
#menu_top-container #menu_mobile-button-burger-icon.visible,
#menu_top-container #menu_mobile-button-close-icon.visible {
  display: block;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_mobile-back {
  display: none;
}
#menu_top-container .hidden {
  height: 0;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_left, #menu_top-container .menu_right {
  box-sizing: border-box;
  height: 100%;
  margin: 0;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_left {
  padding: 1em 0px;
  padding-left: 40px;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_left li.active {
  background: #e5e5e5;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_left li a {
  display: flex;
  width: 100%;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_left li a svg {
  display: none;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_left li:not(.header) a {
  color: var(--cds-text-02, #525252);
  padding: 6px var(--cds-spacing-05, 1rem);
  text-align: left;
  text-decoration: none;
  width: 100%;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_left li.header {
  margin: 1em 0;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_left li.header:hover a {
  background: none;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_left li.header a {
  align-items: center;
  color: #161616;
  display: flex;
  padding: 1rem;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-size: 110%;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_left .bottom-links-container {
  align-items: center;
  display: flex;
  margin-top: var(--cds-spacing-07, 2rem);
  padding: 1rem 0;
  text-decoration: none;
  width: 100%;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_left .bottom-links-container li {
  width: 100%;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_left .bottom-links-container li a {
  color: #054ada;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_right {
  border-left: 1px solid #b5b5b5;
  padding: 1em;
  width: 100%;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_right_subtitle {
  padding: 0 1em;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_right .menu_right-title a {
  color: #054ada;
  font-size: 24px;
  padding: 1rem;
  text-decoration: underline;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_right .menu_right-title.current a {
  color: #323232;
  text-decoration: none;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_sub-links {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  justify-content: space-between;
  padding: 0;
  margin: 0;
}
#menu_top-container div.menu_sub_links_list {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  width: 30%;
}
#menu_top-container div.menu_sub_links_list li {
  box-sizing: border-box;
  width: 100%;
}
#menu_top-container div.menu_sub_links_list li > p {
  margin: 0 0.2em;
}
#menu_top-container div.menu_sub_links_list li.title a, #menu_top-container div.menu_sub_links_list li.title p.menu_right-section-title,
#menu_top-container div.menu_sub_links_list li p.menu_right-section-title {
  font-weight: 700;
}
#menu_top-container div.menu_sub_links_list li a, #menu_top-container div.menu_sub_links_list li p {
  font-size: 100%;
  padding: 6px 1em;
}
#menu_top-container div.menu_sub_links_list li a.menu_banner:hover, #menu_top-container div.menu_sub_links_list li p.menu_banner:hover {
  background: none;
}
#menu_top-container div.menu_sub_links_list li a.menu_banner img, #menu_top-container div.menu_sub_links_list li p.menu_banner img {
  width: 100%;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_button > a {
  text-decoration: none;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_button svg {
  transition: all 0.2s;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_button svg.rotated {
  transform: rotate(180deg);
}
#menu_top-container .menu_sub {
  display: none;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_sub.home-link > * {
  max-width: 80%;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_sub.home-link .menu_right-title a span:last-child {
  height: fit-content;
  margin: auto 0.25em;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_sub.home-link li a:not(.menu_mobile-back) {
  align-items: center;
  color: #161616;
  display: flex;
  text-decoration: none;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_sub.home-link li a:not(.menu_mobile-back) > span {
  max-width: 100%;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_sub.home-link li a:not(.menu_mobile-back) > svg {
  min-width: 1rem;
  margin-left: 0.5rem;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_sub.home-link li.title a:not(.menu_mobile-back) > span {
  width: fit-content;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_sub.home-link li:not(.title) a:not(.menu_mobile-back) {
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  color: #054ada;
  font-weight: 400;
  line-height: 1.25rem;
  letter-spacing: 0;
}
#menu_top-container .menu_sub.home-link > p {
  font-size: 16px;
  text-decoration: none;
  color: #000;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
#menu_top-container .slide-left {
  transform: translateX(-1000%);
}
#menu_top-container .slide-right {
  transform: translateX(1000%);
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  #menu_top-container {
    padding: 1em;
  }
  #menu_top-container #menu_overlay.visible {
    display: none;
  }
  #menu_top-container #menu_overlay.mobile-visible {
    display: block;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_root {
    height: fit-content;
    min-height: 95%;
    position: absolute;
    grid-template-columns: 100%;
    top: 0;
    width: 100%;
    /*
    #menu_close_button {
      display: none;
    }
    */
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_mobile_icon {
    display: block;
  }
  #menu_top-container #menu_mobile-button {
    display: flex;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }
  #menu_top-container #menu_mobile-button > * {
    margin: auto;
  }
  #menu_top-container #menu_buttons_container {
    display: none;
    flex-direction: column;
    left: -1000%;
    position: fixed;
  }
  #menu_top-container #menu_buttons_container.visible {
    background: white;
    box-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2) 0px 2px 6px;
    display: flex;
    height: calc(100vh - 3em);
    min-width: 300px;
    left: 0;
    top: 3em;
  }
  #menu_top-container #menu_buttons_container.visible.admin-toolbar {
    top: 5.5em;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_sub.home-link > *,
  #menu_top-container .menu_sub.home-link .menu_right-title a {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 100%;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_sub.home-link .menu_sub_links_list li > p:not(.menu_right-section-title) {
    display: none;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_container:hover {
    background: #e5e5e5;
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_container,
  #menu_top-container .menu_left > li {
    padding: 0 1em;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_left {
    padding-left: 0;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_left .bottom-links-container {
    padding: 0 1em;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_container .menu_button,
  #menu_top-container .menu_left > li:not(.menu_mobile-back):not(.header) a,
  #menu_top-container .menu_sub-links .menu_sub_links_list li a,
  #menu_top-container .menu_sub_links_list li p.menu_right-section-title,
  #menu_top-container .menu_left .bottom-links-container li a {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--cds-ui-03, #e0e0e0);
    padding: 1rem 0;
    display: flex;
    font: inherit;
    font-weight: inherit;
    width: 100%;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }
  #menu_top-container .back-container {
    display: block;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_left {
    width: 100%;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_button,
  #menu_top-container .menu_left > li {
    box-sizing: border-box;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    width: 100%;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_left li a svg {
    display: initial;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_left li:not(.menu_mobile-back) a svg,
  #menu_top-container .menu_button svg {
    transform: rotate(-90deg);
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_right {
    height: 100%;
    position: absolute;
    right: 100%;
    padding: 0;
    padding-top: 1em;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_right.visible {
    background: white;
    box-shadow: none;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    width: 100%;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_container li.menu_mobile-back {
    display: block;
    padding: 0;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_container li.menu_mobile-back a {
    color: var(--cds-link-01, #0f62fe);
    display: flex;
    padding: 1em var(--cds-spacing-05, 1rem);
    text-align: left;
    text-decoration: none;
    width: 100%;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_container li.menu_mobile-back svg {
    margin: auto 0;
    transform: rotate(90deg);
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_mobile-back:focus-within {
    border: 2px solid;
    border-color: var(--cds-focus, #0f62fe);
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_right .menu_right-title a,
  #menu_top-container .menu_left li.header a {
    font: inherit;
    font-weight: 700;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--cds-ui-04, #8d8d8d);
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_left li.header {
    padding: 0;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_right .menu_right-title {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    text-decoration: none;
    width: 100%;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_right .menu_right-title a {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_right_subtitle {
    display: none;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_sub-links {
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_sub-links li a {
    font-weight: inherit;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_sub-links > .menu_sub_links_list {
    width: 100%;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_sub-links > .menu_sub_links_list > li {
    padding: 0 var(--cds-spacing-05, 1rem);
    width: 100%;
  }
  #menu_top-container .menu_left .bottom-links-container {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

<script charset="utf-8">const defaultSearchTemplate = `
<slot>
  <div id="ibmc-search-input-container" role="search" class="bx--search bx--search--xl bx--search--light">
    <label id="ibmc-search-input-label" class="bx--label" for="ibmc-search-input">Search</label>
    <input class="bx--search-input ibmc-search-input" type="search" autocomplete="off" id="ibmc-search-input" placeholder="Search for your favorite topic">
    <svg focusable="false" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="bx--search-magnifier" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true" style="will-change: transform;">
      <path d="M15,14.3L10.7,10c1.9-2.3,1.6-5.8-0.7-7.7S4.2,0.7,2.3,3S0.7,8.8,3,10.7c2,1.7,5,1.7,7,0l4.3,4.3L15,14.3z M2,6.5	C2,4,4,2,6.5,2S11,4,11,6.5S9,11,6.5,11S2,9,2,6.5z"></path>
    </svg>
    <div class="bx--loading ibmc-search-loading">
      <svg class="bx--loading__svg" viewBox="-75 -75 150 150">
        <title>Loading</title>
        <circle class="bx--loading__stroke" cx="0" cy="0" r="37.5"></circle>
      </svg>
    </div>
      <button
        id="ibmcommunity-search-button-submit"
        class="bx--btn bx--btn--ghost bx--btn--icon-only bx--btn--field ibmc-search-button-submit"
        type="button"
      >
        <svg
          focusable="false"
          preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet"
          style="willChange: 'transform'"
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="bx--btn__icon" width="16" height="16"
          viewBox="0 0 32 32" aria-hidden="true"
        >
          <polygon
            points="18 6 16.57 7.393 24.15 15 4 15 4 17 24.15 17 16.57 24.573 18 26 28 16 18 6"
          />
        </svg>
      </button>
      <div class="bx--dropdown__wrapper ibmc-search-results-wrapper" aria-selector="search-results-container">
        <div class="bx--dropdown bx--dropdown--light bx--dropdown--open">
        </div>
      </div>
  </div>
</slot>
`;

class IBMCommunitySearch extends HTMLElement {
  constructor() {
    super();
    this.rendered = false;
    this.searchResults = [];
    this.isSearchResultsListVisible = false;
    this.timeout = false;
    this.isLoading = false;
    this.controller = new AbortController(); // Added initialization of controller
  }

  static get observedAttributes() {
    return [
      'data-identifier',
    ];
  }

  handleDocumentClick(e) {
    if (this.searchContainerEl && !this.searchContainerEl.contains(e.composedPath()[0])) {
      if (this.isSearchResultsListVisible) {
        this.isSearchResultsListVisible = false;
      }
    }

    if (this.filterContainerEl && !this.filterContainerEl.contains(e.composedPath()[0])) {
      if (this.communityFiltersVisible) {
        this.communityFiltersVisible = false;
      }
    }
  }

  buildBrowserSearchUrl(val) {
    let url = 'https://community.ibm.com/community/user';
    if (this.selectedCommunityFilterIndex === 0) { // this community
      if (this.currentCommunity !== '') {
        url += `/${this.currentCommunity}`;
      }
    }
    url += `/search?executeSearch=true&SearchTerm=${val}`;
    return url;
  }

  buildSearchUrl(val) {
    let query = `http://localhost:8001/hl/search?keywords=${val}`;
    if (this.selectedCommunityFilterIndex === 0 && this.currentCommunity !== '') {
      query += `&filter=${this.currentCommunity}`;
    } else if (this.selectedCommunityFilterIndex === 1) {
      query += '&filter=all';
    }
    return query;
  }

  async getBrowserSearchResults(val, signal) {
    try {
      this.isLoading = true;

      const url = this.buildBrowserSearchUrl(val);
      const res = await fetch(url, { signal });

      const data = await res.text();

      const parser = new DOMParser();
      const domContent = parser.parseFromString(data, 'text/html');
      const resultElements = domContent.querySelectorAll('[id^="FacetedSearchResult"]');

      const arr = [].slice.call(resultElements).slice(0, 5);
      const out = [];

      arr.forEach((el) => {
        const $div = el.querySelector('h3 > div.hl-type > span');
        const $a = el.querySelector('h3 > a');
        let type = '';

        for (const child of $div.childNodes) {
          if (child.nodeType === Node.TEXT_NODE) {
            type += child.textContent;
          }
        }

        const title = $a.textContent.trim();
        const $url = $a.getAttribute('href');

        out.push({ type, title, url: $url });
      });
      this.searchResults = out;
    } catch (e) {
      console.error('Error searching: \n', e);
    } finally {
      this.isLoading = false;
      this.isSearchResultsListVisible = true;
      this.render();
      const input = this.querySelector('#ibmc-search-input');

      if (input) {
        setTimeout(() => {
          input.focus();
        }, 1);
      }
    }
  }

  async debouncedSearch() {
    if (this.timeout) {
      clearTimeout(this.timeout);
      this.timeout = false;
    }

    this.timeout = setTimeout(async () => {
      const { signal } = this.controller; // Changed 'controller' to 'this.controller'
      await this.getBrowserSearchResults(this.searchText, signal);
    }, 300);
  }

  searchTextWatchHandler(val) {
    try {
      if (val.length > 0) {
        if (this.isLoading) {
          this.controller.abort('User still typing'); // Changed 'controller' to 'this.controller'
          this.controller = new AbortController(); // Added initialization of controller
        }

        this.debouncedSearch(val);
      } else {
        this.searchResults = [];
        this.isSearchResultsListVisible = false;
      }
    } catch (e) {
      console.error('Error running debounced search: \n', e);
    }
  }

  handleSearchInputOnInput(e) {
    this.searchText = e.target.value.trim();
    this.searchTextWatchHandler(this.searchText);
  }

  handleSearchInputKeyUp(e) {
    if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.keyCode === 13) {
      const searchUrl = this.buildBrowserSearchUrl(this.searchText);
      window.open(searchUrl, '_self');
    }
  }

  handleSearchInputOnClick() {
    this.isSearchResultsListVisible = this.searchResults.length > 0;
  }

  handleResultListClick(e) {
    console.log('e', e.target);

    const liElement = e.target.closest('li[data-url]');

    if (liElement) {
      this.isSearchResultsListVisible = false;
      window.open(liElement.getAttribute('data-url'), '_self');
    }
  }

  createTemplate() {
    const template = document.createElement('template');
    template.id = 'ibmcommunity-leadspace';
    template.innerHTML = defaultSearchTemplate;

    return template;
  }

  render() {
    if (this.rendered) {
      this.innerHTML = '';
    }

    let template = document.getElementById('ibmcommunity-search');

    if (!template) {
      template = this.createTemplate();
    }

    const templateContent = template.content;

    this.appendChild(templateContent.cloneNode(true));

    const SearchInput = this.querySelector('input.bx--search-input.ibmc-search-input');
    const SubmitButton = this.querySelector('#ibmcommunity-search-button-submit');

    if (this.rendered) {
      SearchInput.value = this.searchText;
    }

    if (SearchInput) {
      SearchInput.addEventListener('click', () => this.handleSearchInputOnClick());
      SearchInput.addEventListener('input', (e) => this.handleSearchInputOnInput(e));
      SearchInput.addEventListener('keyup', (e) => this.handleSearchInputKeyUp(e));
    }

    if (SubmitButton) {
      SubmitButton.addEventListener('click', () => this.handleSearchInputOnClick());
    }

    const SearchResultsContainer = this.querySelector('[aria-selector="search-results-container"]');

    if (!SearchResultsContainer) {
      return;
    }

    if (this.searchResults && this.searchResults.length > 0) {
      if (this.rendered) {
        SearchResultsContainer.innerHTML = '';
      }

      const SearchResultsUl = document.createElement('ul');

      SearchResultsUl.setAttribute('role', 'menu');
      SearchResultsUl.setAttribute('class', 'bx--dropdown-list');
      SearchResultsUl.setAttribute('tabindex', '0');
      SearchResultsUl.setAttribute('aria-hidden', 'true');
      SearchResultsUl.setAttribute('wh-menu-anchor', 'left');
      SearchResultsUl.addEventListener('click', (e) => this.handleResultListClick(e));

      this.searchResults.forEach((item) => {
        console.log('item', item)
        SearchResultsUl.innerHTML += (`
          <li
            data-value="${item.title}"
            data-url="${item.url}"
            class="bx--dropdown-item"
            title="${item.title}"
          >
              <div class="bx--dropdown-link" tabindex="-1">
                <div class="ibmc-results-item-info">
                  <div class="ibmc-results-item-info-type">${item.type}</div>
                  <div class="ibmc-results-item-info-title">${item.title}</div>
                </div>
                <svg focusable="false" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet"
                  style="willChange: 'transform'"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="bx--btn__icon"
                  width="16"
                  height="16"
                  viewBox="0 0 32 32" aria-hidden="true"
                >
                  <polygon points="18 6 16.57 7.393 24.15 15 4 15 4 17 24.15 17 16.57 24.573 18 26 28 16 18 6"/>
                </svg>
              </div>
          </li>
        `);
      });

      SearchResultsContainer.appendChild(SearchResultsUl);
    } else {
      SearchResultsContainer.style.display = 'none';
    }

    this.rendered = true;
  }

  connectedCallback() {
    if (!this.rendered) {
      this.render();
    }

    document.addEventListener('click', (e) => this.handleDocumentClick(e));
  }
}

document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
  if (!window.customElements.get('ibmcommunity-search')) {
    window.customElements.define('ibmcommunity-search', IBMCommunitySearch);
  }
});

// For testing
try {
  module.exports = IBMCommunitySearch;
} catch (e) {}</script>

                        <p><em>Estimated reading time: 6 minutes</em></p>
<p>This week, and based on current information as of the time of publication, <span><a href="https://www.solarwinds.com/securityadvisory" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SolarWinds announced a cyberattack</a></span> that inserted a vulnerability into the SolarWinds<sup>®</sup> Orion<sup>®</sup> Platform software builds for versions 2019.4 HF 5, 2020.2 with no hotfix installed, and 2020.2 HF 1.&nbsp; This vulnerability could enable an attacker to compromise the server(s) on which SolarWinds runs, and thus gain a foothold in the victim’s network. Post compromise, the attacker can conduct lateral movement, data exfiltration and other threat activity.</p>
<p>The United States Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency (CISA) has published <span><a href="https://cyber.dhs.gov/ed/21-01/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Emergency Directive 21-101</a></span>, advising Federal agencies to disconnect or power down all SolarWinds Orion products until further notice.&nbsp;</p>
<p>As with the <span><a href="https://community.ibm.com/community/user/security/blogs/gladys-koskas1/2020/12/10/fireeye-red-team-tools-detection-in-qradar?CommunityKey=f9ea5420-0984-4345-ba7a-d93b4e2d4864&amp;tab=recentcommunityblogsdashboard" target="_blank" rel="noopener">'FireEye Red Team Tools detection in QRadar’ blog</a></span>, in this blog we’ll provide guidance that can help you use QRadar to respond quickly.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>This blog will cover the following topics and content extensions:</p>
<ul>
<li>Threat Intelligence
<ul>
<li><span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/IBMQRadar:ThreatIntelligence" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IBM QRadar Threat Intelligence App</a></span><span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/IBMQRadar:ThreatIntelligence" target="_blank" rel="noopener"></a></span></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Snort Rules
<ul>
<li><span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/b98a9deaac6b7a4e32a54b68a7f9da5d" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IBM Security QRadar Custom Properties for Snort</a></span></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>MD5, SHA-1 and SHA-256<span></span>
<ul>
<li><span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/IBMQRadar:MicrosoftWindowsCustomProperties" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IBM QRadar Custom Properties for Microsoft Windows</a></span><span></span></li>
<li><span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/8f8e1caf1b9decd70542ef741d7d6818" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IBM QRadar Custom Properties for Cisco AMP</a></span><span></span></li>
<li><span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/efb43ce66be214dfee8c549c1e8e8e57" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IBM QRadar Custom Properties for McAfee EPO</a></span><span></span></li>
<li><span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/c8e594fa5d744dcb23859a8fb060bc9d" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IBM QRadar Custom Properties for Windows Defender ATP</a></span><span></span></li>
<li><span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/79449a113bd330507270f9664661d98d" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IBM QRadar Custom Properties for Carbon Black Response</a></span></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Pipe creation and Sysmon<span></span>
<ul>
<li><span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/IBMQRadar:MicrosoftWindowsCustomProperties" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IBM QRadar Custom Properties for Microsoft Windows</a></span></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Endpoint content extension
<ul>
<li><span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/98a27a306371909e1d96ef903676cbb2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IBM QRadar Endpoint Content Extension</a></span></li>
<li><span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/IBMQRadar:MicrosoftWindowsCustomProperties" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IBM QRadar Custom Properties for Microsoft Windows</a></span></li>
<li><span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/427f5d543cb917916619e6abafc26404" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IBM QRadar Custom Properties for Linux</a></span></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><span>Threat Monitoring Content Extension</span>
<ul>
<li><span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/IBMQRadar:IBMContentPackageInternalThreat" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IBM QRadar Security Threat Monitoring Content Extension</a></span></li>

<h2>Threat Intelligence&nbsp;</h2>
<p>IBM Security X-Force researchers published a <span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/collection/DHS-Issues-SolarWinds-Orion-Code-Compromise-Emergency-Directive-48eef2fb4d7e308f0676837b818b5694" target="_blank" rel="noopener">collection of IOCs</a></span>, including malicious file hashes, IP addresses and URLs, connected to this on-going threat.&nbsp; These IOCs can easily be brought into QRadar using the <span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/IBMQRadar:ThreatIntelligence" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Threat Intelligence App</a></span>, which can be downloaded either from <span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IBM Security App Exchange</a></span> or natively via the <span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/ed8aee4440f98f9c8bedaff4c5c644de" target="_blank" rel="noopener">QRadar Assistant</a></span>.&nbsp; Threat indicators can be added to a reference set so that they can be used within building blocks, rules and searches to detect the presence of these IOCs within your environment. Public X-Force Collections, including this one, are free to existing QRadar customers.</p>
<p>QRadar customers who also subscribe to the IBM Security X-Force <span><a href="https://www.ibm.com/products/xforce-exchange/details" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Advanced Threat Protection Feed</a></span> have access to a built-in “Am I Affected?” featured with the Threat Intelligence app. This tool can be used in tandem with other forms of threat intelligence that may become available in this developing situation to help assess known IOCs.&nbsp; With this subscription, new X-Force collections are loaded directly into QRadar, and users can simply click ‘Scan now’ to automatically search for all IOCs associated with a collection. The query results will show you which systems and users may have been connected to this threat, assisting you to initiate investigation, remediation and response.</p>
<p><img src="https://higherlogicdownload.s3.amazonaws.com/IMWUC/UploadedImages/84c2c9a3-e7dd-4205-a95f-bba9a25415fa/spotligh2.png" alt="spotligh2.png" data-mce-hlimagekey="e7889ba7-4810-8eba-79d7-982d819a1d23" data-mce-hlselector="#MainCopy_ctl04_tmceEditor_TinyMCEContent" class="img-responsive"></p>
<p>If you do not currently subscribe to the Advanced Threat Protection Feed, a <span><a href="https://www.ibm.com/account/reg/us-en/signup?formid=urx-40692" target="_blank" rel="noopener">30-day free trial</a></span> is available.</p>
<p>
</p><h2>Snort Rules</h2>
<p>Once again, FireEye and Cisco Talos teams provided a new set of Snort rules to implement. QRadar users can easily create a new rule based on these signatures, correlate these insights with other events, or optionally be alerted directly via email. The steps to implement this are:</p>
<ol>
<li>&nbsp;Install the <span><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/b98a9deaac6b7a4e32a54b68a7f9da5d" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IBM Security QRadar Custom Properties for Snort</a></span> content extension</li>
<li>Create a new Event rule</li>
</ol>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%" border="1">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="width: 100%">
<p><span style="font-size: 8pt">Apply <strong>Sunburst</strong><strong> - Snort Rules</strong> on events which are detected by the Local system</span><br><span style="font-size: 8pt">and when the event(s) were detected by one or more of <strong>Snort Open Source IDS</strong></span><br><span style="font-size: 8pt">and when the event matches <strong>"Rule ID" in (</strong><strong>77600832,77600833,77600842,77600843,77600844,77600845,77600846,77600847,77600848,77600850,77600851,77600852,77600853,77600854,77600855,77600868,<br>77600840,77600863,77600864,77600865,77600837,77600856,77600857,77600858,77600859,77600860,77600866,56660,56661,56662,56663,56664,56665,56666,56667,56668) AQL filter query</strong></span><span style="font-size: 8pt"><strong></strong></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>
</p><h2>MD5, SHA-1 and SHA-256</h2>
<p>We talked about it, file hashes are a great source to improve threat detection. Once again, you can have a quick implementation by enabling detection with MD5, SHA-1 and SHA-256 through three reference sets and one custom rule.</p>
<ol>
<li>&nbsp;Create three Reference Sets, one per hash type, and populate them with the <a href="//higherlogicdownload.s3.amazonaws.com/IMWUC/UploadedImages/c9bd8668-d409-43ad-b26f-38a261105238/Sunburst_md5">Sunburst_md5</a>, <a href="//higherlogicdownload.s3.amazonaws.com/IMWUC/UploadedImages/c9bd8668-d409-43ad-b26f-38a261105238/Sunburst_sha1">Sunburst_sha1</a>, <a href="//higherlogicdownload.s3.amazonaws.com/IMWUC/UploadedImages/c9bd8668-d409-43ad-b26f-38a261105238/Sunburst_sha256">Sunburst_sha256</a> files (comma separated).<br>
<p class="media" style="overflow: hidden"><img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/W6zmU1vTcSQDHsOuqCYq_temp.png" class="media-object tinymce-editor-img img-responsive" data-title="" data-modalsrc="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/W6zmU1vTcSQDHsOuqCYq_temp.png" data-imgbase="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/W6zmU1vTcSQDHsOuqCYq_temp.png" data-imgthumbnail="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/W6zmU1vTcSQDHsOuqCYq_temp-T.jpg" data-imgmedium="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/W6zmU1vTcSQDHsOuqCYq_temp-M.jpg" data-imglarge="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/W6zmU1vTcSQDHsOuqCYq_temp-L.jpg"><br><br></p>
<p class="media" style="overflow: hidden"><img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/JYARJBh8SCGk3fpwazVL_temp.png" class="media-object tinymce-editor-img img-responsive" data-title="" data-modalsrc="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/JYARJBh8SCGk3fpwazVL_temp.png" data-imgbase="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/JYARJBh8SCGk3fpwazVL_temp.png" data-imgthumbnail="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/JYARJBh8SCGk3fpwazVL_temp-T.jpg" data-imgmedium="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/JYARJBh8SCGk3fpwazVL_temp-M.jpg" data-imglarge="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/JYARJBh8SCGk3fpwazVL_temp-L.jpg"></p>
</li>
<li>Install content extensions containing Hash properties or create your own.<br>On the App Exchange, you can find MD5, SHA-1 and SHA-256 parsed for the following devices:<br><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/79449a113bd330507270f9664661d98d" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Carbon Black Response</a>, <a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/8f8e1caf1b9decd70542ef741d7d6818" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cisco AMP</a>, <a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/efb43ce66be214dfee8c549c1e8e8e57" target="_blank" rel="noopener">McAfee ePolicy Orchestrator</a>, <a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/c8e594fa5d744dcb23859a8fb060bc9d" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Microsoft Windows Defender ATP</a>, <a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/IBMQRadar:MicrosoftWindowsCustomProperties" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Microsoft Windows Security Event Log</a></li>
<li>Create a rule that tests the Custom Properties <em>MD5 Hash</em>, <em>Parent MD5</em>, <em>SHA1 Hash</em>, <em>Parent SHA1 Hash</em>, <em>SHA256 Hash</em>, <em>Parent SHA256 Hash</em> against the new Reference Sets.<br>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%" border="1">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="width: 100%"><span style="font-size: 8pt">Apply <strong>Sunburst - Tools Hash</strong> on events which are detected by the Local system</span><br><span style="font-size: 8pt">and when the event(s) were detected by one or more of <strong>Carbon Black Response, Cisco AMP, McAfee ePolicy Orchestrator, Microsoft Windows Defender ATP, Microsoft Windows Security Event Log</strong></span><br><span style="font-size: 8pt">and when the event matches <strong>("MD5 Hash" IS NOT NULL AND REFERENCESETCONTAINS('Sunburst - MD5', "MD5 Hash")) OR ("Parent MD5" IS NOT NULL AND REFERENCESETCONTAINS('Sunburst - MD5', "Parent MD5")) OR ("SHA1 Hash" IS NOT NULL AND REFERENCESETCONTAINS('Sunburst - SHA1', "SHA1 Hash")) OR ("Parent SHA1 Hash" IS NOT NULL AND REFERENCESETCONTAINS('Sunburst - MD5', "Parent SHA1 Hash")) OR ("SHA256 Hash" IS NOT NULL AND REFERENCESETCONTAINS('Sunburst - SHA256', "SHA256 Hash")) OR ("Parent SHA256 Hash" IS NOT NULL AND REFERENCESETCONTAINS('Sunburst - SHA256', "Parent SHA256 Hash"))</strong> AQL filter query</span></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<br>

</li>

<h2>Pipe creation and Sysmon</h2>
<p>In the blog<span></span> published by FireEye regarding SUNBURST, there is a mention about the creation of a pipe named&nbsp;<em>583da945-62af-10e8-4902-a8f205c72b2e</em> as one of the “delivery and installation” mechanism:</p>
<p class="media" style="overflow: hidden"><img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/y19vvp6hT4K0Nl1srDLT_temp.png" class="media-object tinymce-editor-img img-responsive" data-title="" data-modalsrc="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/y19vvp6hT4K0Nl1srDLT_temp.png" data-imgbase="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/y19vvp6hT4K0Nl1srDLT_temp.png" data-imgthumbnail="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/y19vvp6hT4K0Nl1srDLT_temp-T.jpg" data-imgmedium="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/y19vvp6hT4K0Nl1srDLT_temp-M.jpg" data-imglarge="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/y19vvp6hT4K0Nl1srDLT_temp-L.jpg"><br><span style="text-decoration: underline">Source</span>: <span><a href="https://www.fireeye.com/blog/threat-research/2020/12/evasive-attacker-leverages-solarwinds-supply-chain-compromises-with-sunburst-backdoor.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Highly Evasive Attacker Leverages SolarWinds Supply Chain to Compromise Multiple Global Victims With SUNBURST Backdoor</a></span></p>
<p>If you are collecting Sysmon logs, you have another opportunity for a quick way to detect another IOC.</p>
<ol>
<li>Download the&nbsp;<u><a href="https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/hub/extension/IBMQRadar:MicrosoftWindowsCustomProperties" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IBM QRadar Custom Properties for Microsoft Windows</a></u> content extension</li>
<li>Create a rule that detects the pipe name mentioned in the blog<br>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%" border="1">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="width: 100%"><span style="font-size: 8pt">Apply <strong>Sunburst - Pipe Name</strong> on events which are detected by the Local system</span><br><span style="font-size: 8pt">and when the event(s) were detected by one or more of <strong>Microsoft Windows Security Event Log</strong></span><br><span style="font-size: 8pt">and when the event <strong>QID is one of the following (5001836) PipeEvent (Pipe Created)</strong></span><br><span style="font-size: 8pt">and when the event matches <strong>PipeName (custom) is any of 583da945-62af-10e8-4902-a8f205c72b2e</strong></span></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</li>
</ol>

</p><h2><span>Threat Monitoring Content Extension</span></h2>
<p>The multi-task pack ! This pack is mentioned last in this blog because it is certainly going to need some tuning to be adapted to what you are looking for, but it is definitely a good help to know where to go.</p>
<p>As an example, thanks to your endpoint security software, you can increase the visibility on a threat spreading through the network. Indeed, this extension contains a series of rules alerting on security software.</p>
<p class="media" style="overflow: hidden"><img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/QqKQihCQb2cemJpflfRA_temp.png" class="media-object tinymce-editor-img img-responsive" data-title="" data-modalsrc="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/QqKQihCQb2cemJpflfRA_temp.png" data-imgbase="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/QqKQihCQb2cemJpflfRA_temp.png" data-imgthumbnail="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/QqKQihCQb2cemJpflfRA_temp-T.jpg" data-imgmedium="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/QqKQihCQb2cemJpflfRA_temp-M.jpg" data-imglarge="https://s3.amazonaws.com/higherlogicdownload/IMWUC/UploadedImages/QqKQihCQb2cemJpflfRA_temp-L.jpg" style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid" alt="QqKQihCQb2cemJpflfRA_temp.png"></p>
<p>All you have to do is to:</p>
<ol>
<li>Ensure your device is listed in one of BB:DeviceDefinition: AV/AM or BB:DeviceDefinition: IDS / IPS Building blocks</li>
<li>Get the Threat Name parsed either by downloading one of our content extension, or creating your own extraction.</li>
</ol>
<p>You can decide to duplicate the rules to focus the detection on SUNBURST specifically, and have a higher priority rule response (email, SNMP trap, vulnerability scan). Simply add a new filter to the original rule, catching the specific Threat Name reported by your product:</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%" border="1">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="width: 100%"><span style="font-size: 8pt">and when the event matches <strong>Threat Name (custom) is any of <em>Backdoor.Sunburst</em></strong></span></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><strong><em>&nbsp;</em></strong></p>
<p>Please refer to your product documentation to get more information on the relevant detection name</p>

<h2>Conclusion</h2>
<p>The above steps can enable you to easily take advantage of the publicly available IOCs and Countermeasures to detect indicators of the SUNBURST threat within your environment.&nbsp; All of the QRadar apps, custom properties and content extensions mentioned above are available free of charge to all QRadar customers and can be downloaded either from the IBM Security App Exchange or natively via QRadar Assistant.</p>
<p>As usual, we build content for you, to save you time and effort, a content that you can use as a base and adapt to your environment and your needs. Don't hesitate to give us any feedback or ideas, tell us what you need.</p>
